cs.CV, cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.MM, cs.IR 

This paper deals with video object segmentation, which is a problem in computer vision. Therefore, the most likely category is cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition). The paper also proposes a fully convolutional network trained by a modified triplet loss, which is a machine learning technique, making cs.LG (Machine Learning) another likely category. Additionally, the paper involves user interaction, which could fall under cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) or cs.MM (Multimedia). Finally, the paper uses a nearest-neighbor approach, which is a common technique in information retrieval, making cs.IR (Information Retrieval) a possible category as well.
